Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Michael> State channels move smart contracts off the blockchain. (re @Matterbridge_kmdbot: [matrix] <jl777:matrix.org> KMD has notary nodes which can create data that performs the function of an oracle, ie. notarizations, MoM, that enables the cross chain contracts. As far as state channels go, what exactly is meant by that and what functionality does it enable that is not possible otherwise?)

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [matrix] <jl777:matrix.org> since we dont have any single giant blockchain, there is no need to use a state channel to move smart contract off the blockchain. our lack of it is not any disadvantage

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [matrix] <jl777:matrix.org> in some sense all state for all contracts can be moved to any other chain in the cluster via MoMoM proofs, so there is the equivalent of state channels

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [matrix] <jl777:matrix.org> just not exactly a state channel
